The paper discusses a specific issue in Prolog programming related to expressing syntactic inequality and proposes a new predicate to overcome the problem. This falls under the area of programming languages and logic programming, which is covered by cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the issue of code complexity and efficiency, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new construct for if-then-else statements, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
